<Review>Reasonably priced and busy. Both good signs for a business and I enjoyed my haircut a lot. My only gripe was I had originally wanted to grow out my hair longer and wanted to do some maintenance on it so I can get it properly layered, but got a bit too much chopped off than I would have liked.

On the bright side, the barber that serviced me had done an excellent job on my hair otherwise. Admittedly, I should've gone to a place that worked with longer hair for men if I had wanted to do what I wanted originally. The barber still did a fantastic job and I would still recommend this place.

One thing to keep in mind though was that the barber I had mainly spoke Spanish so it was a bit hard to ask what I wanted from her. There were other barbers that were able to pitch in and translate for me though.<//Review></record>

<time>1574366983006<//time>< Rating>
5<//Rating>
< Review>
Not the best pizza I've had, but it was good. The wings though, were amazing! The staff is super friendly. The guy who helped us was very nice.  Quick service. We got wings, and a small pizza, and 2 drinks, and it was about 30 bucks.

Clean inside. It wasn't too busy. 4 or 5 people trickled in while we were there. They have 4 televisions playing different things. And a cute, small arcade for kids.

There is a small salad bar. I believe for 7 dollars. The basics, and some macaroni salad. I wouldn't say it's worth 7 dollars though. It was a very small selection.

Bathroom was surprisingly clean. Not to say it should not be. Bit most places you go, the bathroom seems to be neglected. Theirs was very clean. I was not so grossed out, as I am with most places.

We will eat here again.< /Review>

<user_name>Pauline Robinson</user_name><Time>1484003829337</Time>< rating>
5<//rating>
< Review>
I like their friendly and approachable personnel, the quality of their products.  I like their packaging. Good for gifts at Christmas and New Year.  I recently placed an order with Fragrant Jerky to send to a relative in L.A. area.  The package was lost (or stolen) en route to the destination.  I later found out that the address was incomplete because I was given the wrong address.  I called up Fragrant and Jeff answered the phone.  I could tell they were real busy from the background noise and Jeff was catching his breath.  I was amazed that he still answered the phone in spite of the hectic holiday orders.  He also called me after work hours as a follow up.  That's what I call PERSONAL TOUCH.  How often you have a life personal answering the phone to talk to you?  And how often you get personal assistance right away particularly during such busy holiday retails.  I have no doubt that Fragrant Jerky will, if not already has, become very successful and keep growing if they maintain their personal touch.  The story does not end there.  Jeff replaced the order without charge and sent it out to my relative the next morning and they received it just in time for the holiday.  I offered to buy for it because it was my fault to have given them an incomplete address causing the loss of the package, but Jeff would not charge it.  They now make a regular customer of me.  I've actually placed two other orders at the same time and each was received promptly.  And all the recipients are happy with the quality and taste.< /Review>

< Text>
Our family unfortunately contracted Covid through our status as essential workers. We are under quarantine and cannot currently leave our house for our normal groceries. So we placed a delivery order from smartandfinal.com. First our order was delayed, a bit inconvenient but not a major problem. Then our order was missing several items....of course it is missing the more expensive meats. Again not a major problem stores are busy this time of year and employees are stretched thin. My main problem arises when we call the store at 545pm and are told we couldn't of placed an order through smart and final online, they don't know about smart and final online and need to call Door Dash. We are put on hold while someone goes to find a manager for clarification. Someone else picks up the phone, not a manager, and says the same thing and says to call back in the morning. No help, no assistance, missing groceries and we cannot leave our house amd of course were were charged our FULL order amount the missing items are still on our bill.

Instead of using this shady ordering system, If you need grocery delivery order from VONS/Albertson they forgot a bag when we ordered from them last week and the same night (930pm) they sent a Door Dash order for the missing items. That is service!</Text>

<userid>111328843500019722668<//userid><user_name>Maureen Horton</user_name><time>1614880536661<//time>< Rate>
5</Rate>
< Text>
My husband and I received a gift card for Iva Lee's for Christmas, from a friend who highly recommended the place.  I'm so glad she introduced us to it!  We had intended to come over the weekend but didn't realize they were closed Sundays and Mondays, so we were really looking forward to having our "dinner date" this Thursday (tonight).

We started with drinks.  I had their old fashioned, while my husband had...I don't remember what it was called but it was the one that included absinthe.  Both drinks were really good!  The old fashioned was a little sweeter than what I'm used to, but not too sweet, and very smooth.  The flavor of the other drink actually reminded me of a more traditional old fashioned.  It was tasty and more potent than expected!

We also had the hush puppies, which were complimentary since we checked in on Yelp.  They were crispy on the outside, creamy on the inside, and the relish and garnishing was absolutely delicious!  I will admit they may have spent just a little too long in the fryer, but they were still really good.

I had the jambalaya as my entree, and I loved it!  It had just a little heat and had tons of chicken (the chicken was just okay), tender shrimp, and flavorful slightly-smoky sausage.  The tomato-based sauce was flavorful and complimented the dish perfectly.  My husband had the braised short ribs, and he was a huge fan!  I tried a bite of it as well.  It was incredibly tender and not over-seasoned.  The meat spoke for itself.  The au gratin potatoes that came with it could have used a tiny bit more salt but they were deliciously creamy and cheesy.  I did not try the veggies that came with his dish but he liked those too.  The portions of both our dishes were spot on.  It wasn't an overwhelming amount of food but it was more than enough to be filling (not overly so) while allowing just enough room for an amazing dessert.

For dessert we had the bread pudding.  Wow!  It came out hot, with the sauce on the side, which was pretty cool because we were able to eat some of the pudding, add some sauce, and so on and so on, so each bite was a nice combination of warm bread pudding and creamy sweet sauce.

The service was good too.  Our server was very friendly, and the food and drinks came out much more quickly than expected.

There was also live music going on.  We weren't too close to that but we could still hear it.  It sounded fantastic and wasn't too loud.  It was a great addition to our whole dinner experience.

Yes, the menu items are a little on the pricey side but we were pleasantly surprised when the bill came.  The drinks were on special, only $8 each, plus our hush puppies were free.  Our bill came out to $86 for an appetizer, two entrees, three drinks, and dessert!  Not cheap but much less than we expected thanks to the Yelp offer and the drink specials.

I would love to come back here on other days when they have specials, for a special occasion, or for a night out to listen to good music while enjoying a couple drinks and maybe some appetizers.< /Text>

<userid>113850642901046320259</userid>< user_name>
John Newdick< /user_name>
<time>1490745270668< /time>< Rating>
5< /Rating>
< Text>
This is my favorite Friday/ Saturday night spot in San Clemente!  Their selection of creole food and southern cooking is outrageous and the bartenders make very good cocktails.  They also feature live blues most nights of the week, a small dance floor, and outstanding service (JC is my favorite).  I bring friends and family here whenever they visit - it's never what they expect to find in a small, southern Cali surf town, but they always love it!!

Expect meals to cost $17-35, cocktails $10.

-Also a great place for most major holidays.  They will have especially talented musicians and offer prix fixe menus...just make sure you book at least a week in advance.<//Text>

< review>
My husband and I came to Iva Lee's last Saturday night. Our whole evening was so much fun!  The food was amazing. The Crab Cakes with Creole Remoulade was delicious.  For dinner, I had the Shrimp n' Grits.  To die for.  My husband is a big meat eater & he can't stop talking about the Grilled Rib-Eye.  I am a big Moscow Mule fan and they had the best I have ever had.  They make their own ginger beer and it has a nice spicy kick.  Our server Alex was so friendly & knowlegeable about the menu.  I don't know how we fit it in, but he highly recommended the Bread Pudding with the Jack Daniels Whisky sauce which was such a treat.  After dinner, we ventured into the lounge for another Moscow Mule & a few dances with the Bayou Brothers.  So much fun!  We will absolutely be back!!!</review>

We ended up getting a great deal and bought two beds, full headboards, side rails, and footboard (beautiful sets) for the same price as one bed would have cost at Sleep Train or Evan's. This is my new go-to furniture store. My new bed will be delivered on Wednesday and they're even going to put it together and recycle my old mattress and box spring. Excellent service (no annoying sales people following you around - they are sincere and let you browse), excellent experience, and overall, excellent on the bank account.<//text>< user_name>

< text>
I had an amazing experience with Ryan last year. His professionalism and experience played a major part in settling a complicated case.
My dad was visiting me from India, he became a victim of pedestrian accident of an under-insured driver. He required a surgery which was quoted at a high price. I decided to consult this case with an injury attorney and that's where Ryan came in to picture.

His arrival relieved stress on our entire family and gave us the confidence upon acknowledging his mastery in the end to end process. He suggested a few surgeons who gave me a few quotes and asked me to chose from.  He made it so simple, he called the doc's office and booked appointments on my behalf.

In the end, i chose a doctor who was not in Ryan's list and Ryan was ready to work with him.

Ryan promptly inquired about my dad's health and spoke with my dad several times amidst his busy schedule. He was also courteous to return calls and emails through out the settlement process.

Because of his involvement, my financial burden reduced and my dad is doing great.  Me and my family sincerely thank him and we know who we need to contact in case something like this comes up in our loved one's life.

In my opinion, it is better to approach PROs instead of taking things in your hand. I used my valuable time helping my dad recover rather than going through balance sheets and talking with collection agencies and hospital billing department< /text>

Jared was always able to explain things to me so that I understood what was going on and what to expect. He was responsive to my phone calls. He could calm me down when I was freaking out. He was easy to talk to and friendly. Occasionally, he wouldn't get messages that I left with the administrative assistant. I don't think that was a Jared problem though. The Sargent Firm helped me sooo much!!!! In the beginning, Allison handled my case and kept me informed the whole time. She told me exactly what would be expected of me, and called and emailed me routinely to fill me in on what I needed to do next. She set up all of my doctors (I chose to go through doctors through the firm) and they took such good care of me!!! I went through six months of doctors appointments and while waiting to get results back Allison did heavy negotiating for me. We were not able to agree on a settlement with Mercury Insurance, so my case was passed on to Jared Pursley. Jared helped me a lot!!! I worked hand in hand with Jared and he would not settle on a number I was not comfortable with. He really pushed for me, and made me feel confident in my decisions. Jared kept in contact with me the whole time and always was so polite and answered my millions of questions. After one year and 8 months we settled on what I had originally wanted thanks to Jared and his hard work!
Thank you so much to the whole team, I am so happy to have this behind me, and I couldn't have done it without you guys!
Joei Bianca< /Review>

< Review>
Brew pub with great beers to choose from, very friendly staff with the owner joint in as well.
We went on a monday, open mike night for the stage, with rotating artists performing mostly classic rock n roll tunes. Very talented crowd of musicians from amateur to semi/ professional. Most of the guys on the stage came to play and have fun as well.
Very homey brew pub with pretty much an all regular crowd in attendance. No complaints at all here, what a great place to hang out at for all. T-shirts and hoodies are also available for sale here. Come hang out and grab a shirt or hoodie.<//Review>

< text>
Such a very cool place. Came here to meet some friends from Temecula, and was pleasantly surprised by how much fun I had! Hidden in an industrial park this place was POPPIN!

Open Mic night is such a blast. It is great to see so many different talented people have the courage to perform in an open setting like this.

The venue is small but cozy. The beer is flowing and tasty. They have that little taqueritta stand that is cooking up some delicious bites.

I really recommend if you are in the area to check this place out. I had the opportunity to see a 12 year old kid shred on the guitar for the first time in front of a crowd, so that alone was pretty cool.

-1 star for being so far away from me and only having one bathroom!<//text>

<rate>1<//rate>< review>
*Updated Review as of 1/4/21*

At the end of my alterations fitting, I was handed a business card with names of the three women who assisted in the fitting and asked if I could leave a positive google review. I said OK, thinking they meant if I was genuinely satisfied and wanted to go out of my way to say something nice after leaving the store. I didn't realize they meant literally right then and there, they wanted me to write the review. I was asked to have a seat while they "updated my information in the system" and that this was "a good time to spend a few minutes writing that five star review" and to let them know when I was finished.  Since they were standing there, literally waiting for me to post the five star review, I felt like I didn't have much of a choice. Never in my life has a business forced me to leave a five star review - it was the most unprofessional and uncomfortable thing I have ever experienced as a customer.

Beware of this David's Bridal - it's super shady that they are forcing customers to write five star reviews! I honestly did not feel comfortable updating this review until my dress was picked up, but needed to put this out there as a warning to others.

Original Review Below - 11/7/20

Jo, Fae, and Sarah in alterations were fast, professional, and extremely helpful. Wonderful and friendly customer service.</review>

< Review>
Cannot say enough good things about this store and my experience so far. I purchased a dress at a boutique out of state where the wedding will be and was planning on having alterations done there. But when the pandemic hit, all original plans went out the window. I ended up having the dress shipped to me but had no idea where to go for alterations. Since I got my own wedding dress at David's Bridal, I knew I would be happy with the experience. Though there was a mishap when scheduling the appointment and I found out, while I was standing in the dressing room, they don't do non-David's Bridal dress alterations, my heart sank. Where else was I to go with such little time left? Could I trust another place to do a good job? Luckily Jo and Fae in alterations said they could make it work, but they just couldn't uphold the same store policies if something were to happen to the dress. Phew. THANK YOU JO AND FAE! They were so kind and understanding of the situation, and I appreciated that they were upfront about any additional costs, etc. I can finally worry about other things since I know my dress is in good hands. My sister just got engaged and I will DEFINITELY be making sure David's Bridal is top of her list for her day.<//Review>

< review>
A close friend asked me to step in as her sister/bridesmaid since neither of her sisters will make it to her wedding. It was on short notice with the wedding a little over a month away. Luckily because of the specific color swatch it helped narrow down the choices for dresses. Joylin was my stylist and she really was a JOY to work with. She was caring and understanding. The dress I would‚Äôve really liked to wear would not have arrived in time so we patiently shopped for similar ones. We settled for a dress I was okay with. Even though I was a bridesmaid she reminded me that I should be happy about my dress too which was a really sweet sentiment to be reminded of. The overall appointment was a great experience. Thank you, Joylin! Your wonderful customer service skills are very much appreciated.

UPDATE: my dress arrived sooner than expected, thankfully. I went in for my fitting and I was greeted by Amara from alterations who measured me and my shoes. Amara is super sweet and personable. Jo did the fitting and pinned what needed to be altered, just the hem and shoulders. She explained that hem seems a bit long but my shoes are not supposed to show. You can tell Jo is experienced, works quickly and is no nonsense. I was a little confused when Jo put the ‚Äúsew by‚Äù date for a date After my event. Sarah patiently explained what Jo meant by a ‚Äúsew by‚Äù date which cleared things up so I wouldn‚Äôt panic about not having my dress on time.  $100+tax for the alterations, I probably could‚Äôve asked my mom to do, but I‚Äôll leave up to the experts. Last update: went in to pick up my dress today. Was helped by Chloe and Sarah. Chloe helped me into my dress for one last try and to make sure everything was good. I‚Äôve been pleased with the whole process for buying a bridesmaid dress here at David‚Äôs Bridal in Burbank.</review>

< text>
With COVID still raging on my fiancee and I decided to have a small wedding, with just one month to plan. With a short time left, I tried shopping online but was so disappointed with what I received so I knew I had to visit a shop. David's Bridal was the only one around that was open so I bravely made an appointment. Fortunately, the whole process was a lot easier than I feared. I made the appointment online, arrived, and they took care of me right away.

Sarah Anne was amazing -- she picked out a variety of styles for me that all looked great. But then she showed me the perfect one and I was able to purchase it on the spot. She also suggested a sash that went really well with the dress. Amara is doing the alterations and she was amazing also! She quickly explained to me what would need to be altered in a clear way and she said it could be done in just two weeks!

I'm so thankful for Sarah Anne and Amara that they were able to match my budget, my fit, and the quick timeline.

Tip: come with some ideas in mind (I made a Pinterest board) but also trust the stylist to choose for you too. They're experts and they know what looks good!</text>

< Review>
TIMING IS EVERYTHING!

The staff at this location is lovely. They are helpful, friendly, and personable. However, there were several challenges with our order arriving in a timely manner. We ordered one (on sale) dress in mid-June, and it didn‚Äôt arrive to the store until the day we needed to pick it up.

I don‚Äôt know if this delay was due to order error or due to COVID-19 shipping challenges, but it made our experience far more stressful than it needed to be. Initially due to arrive on 7/13/2020, the dress was rescheduled to arrive on 7/20/2020, but actually arrived after our alterations appointment on 7/21/2020. Since we needed the alterations done by 7/21/2020, management waved the up-charge for same day alterations.

The most disappointing thing about our experience was the cost for the alteration, which included a straight seam to shorten the dress on two layers of (delicate) fabric. The fee for this alteration was significantly more than the cost of the dress, and, for the cost of the alteration alone, we could have purchased a similar dress from a department store for less that would have included basic alterations (like shortening the hem length).

Don‚Äôt get me wrong! The alterations staff was lovely, and I am certain they will do a fantastic job (we have not picked up the altered dress, yet). However, if you can get your dress in a timely manner, perhaps you will have the choice of whether to use David‚Äôs Bridal‚Äôs on-site alterations or an alterations source of your own choosing. Were I to have received the dress in a timely manner, I would definitely have found a more affordable alterations source (several I have used in the past come to mind).

2020 chaos doesn‚Äôt cease to exist at David‚Äôs Bridal this year.

The good news is we have a dress that‚Äôs the right color and style for our Junior Bridesmaid‚Äôs wedding appearance this weekend. Phew!< /Review>

I said YES to the dress!!!

I walked into my bridal appointment with no idea what I wanted. I had looked at many styles online and had things that I liked, but I did not know what I wanted or would be best for me. I brought my mom, sister, and one of my bridesmaids with me. When we arrived we spent a bit of time browsing what was there and discussing what might work for me. Sarah Ann listened to what I thought and told me that I needed to be open and trust her. She pulled some of the initial dresses I pointed out. She was excellent at choosing dresses that were flattering on my body and within my price range. As I tried on more dresses we started getting a better idea of what was the right one. She also brought "different" styles to help me see what I liked and didn't like about other styles. It was totally the dress, not at all what I thought I would choose, but it was perfect for me!

<user_id>106525524351661532969< /user_id><Name>Shona Potrzuski<//Name>< Date>

<Rating>5< /Rating><Text>Call me crazy for continuing with my wedding during COVID, but 70 days out from my wedding date I found myself at David's bridal trying on dresses for the first time. I new I would have 1 hour with my stylist to look for dresses, but did not know that I would be limited to only trying on 5 in that hour. It was never mentioned on their website nor did anyone mention this on the phone when they called me to confirm the appointment. When booking the appointment online I was asked a ton of questions about what sort of dress I was looking for, and even asked to supply a pinterest page, but it seemed to me that none of that was shared with the stylist beforehand, so I thought that was a waste of time. Otherwise, despite all this covid nonsense I really enjoyed my fitting. I brought one friend with me (you could bring up to two) and we were asked to sanitize our hands and then put on a pair of latex gloves before browsing the available dress section. They had taken a sample dress of each one they had in the store and placed them in one centralized area to browse through and asked that you didn't take it off the rack. The stylist would then go and grab the dresses you liked in your size from a separate section that wasn't available to the general public, and walked you to the fitting room. While the stylist didn't come into the fitting room with you, you could request assistance from a friend or the stylist (ex - zip up). I had trouble getting a dress over my head and was able to bring my friend in to help pull it down. They are steaming gowns in between shoppers and doing so in a highly visible area. I watched my stylist bring my dresses to be cleaned right after I exited the changing room, so that was reassuring. Personally I didn't spend more than 5 minutes in each dress, so I had time to try on a 5th dress but chose not to and will be returning for a second visit to narrow down my search, and my stylist took down notes on which dresses I'll be trying on again and the couple I suggested for next time. My stylist wasn't intrusive and gave me a lot of space. She was unbiased and didn't lean towards one dress or another, though when I did comment on things I didn't like she did suggest ways to improve the dress to my liking and assured that due to David's bridal's internal seamstress/tailoring team that any alterations could be made relatively quickly.

Edit: returned to DB on 9/9 for my dress fitting. My dress and veil arrived two weeks early, but I kept the appointment on the 9th. Jo and her assistant Amara were wonderful and made me feel right at home despite COVID. Extra precautions were made including wearing gloves in addition to masks when pinning my dress. Jo showed both me (and my roommate who will be assisting me on the big day) how to get the petticoat into the dress and how to step into both, she made everything very easy and simple! She showed me various options and made suggestions as to how she would advise pinning, hemming, and altering the dress, and left the decisions totally up to me.  I was charmed with engaging conversation and laughs, and holy moly you wouldn't believe what Jo did with my bustle! Amara counted 11 points! It looks like ornate frosting on a cake - I could just eat it! SO excited to pick up my dress in a few weeks and see the final product.

Picked up the dress from alterations and it is gorgeous! Had my veil steamed as well. Cant believe the big day is one week away. Thanks to everyone and DB who made this a positive experience during all the covid nonsense!< /Text>< pictures>
None</pictures>

< Text>
I was completely blown away by my experience here. It was my first time ever trying on dresses, I've been waiting since everything closed in March!

I figured I'd start with David's bridal because they have longer appointment times than smaller boutiques, I wasn't expecting much. But I got set up with Brooke as a consultant, and she is literally a dream.

It was complete 1-1 help, she knew I hadn't even so much as touched a dress before, so we went through my Pinterest and walked the store. She knew my size instantly just by looking at me, and picked out dresses I actually want to try on.

Each dress I tried was better than the next one! And this is a tribute to Brooke, because she listened to me describe what I liked and it was like I got an upgrade on each new gown. I was worried I'd have this experience of "well none of them fit or looked good but at least I got the first session out of the way", but instead what I experienced was "how on Earth am I going to choose they're all beautiful".

Even my dad, who took the place of my MOH today who couldn't make this appointment, was super into it because he loves good business practices (men, right?) And Brooke was super sweet with my mom as well.

It was the best first experience I could have in a bridal store, and it got me so excited for my weekend of bridal appointments. I already scheduled a follow up on Sunday because I have a feeling even after trying a few other stores I'll want to come back to Brooke. (We ended the session on a dress that made my mom cry out of happiness).

I can't recommend this store enough, you HAVE to stop by here and hang with Brooke if you're looking for dresses!</Text>

< text>
This has been the worst experience of my year wasted at David's Bridal. At first I wasn't going to waste my breath, but future brides should have warning.
First visit Oct 2019, Sara Anne - employee, playing tug a war, LITERALLY, with my mother in law over a chair. When clearly the manager, STEPHANIE, stated that she was giving us chairs. Moved us from one section to another so a larger party can fit. Initially I made sure to contact the Burbank location of the number of guest I will be bringing and that there would be accommodated. Ended with a dress that I had to add sleeves to. Dress was $400. Expressed my frustrations with Stephanie of the limited variety of dresses she was able to offer when there were plenty online she could've suggested if they weren't in stock at the store. She offers "10%" off. A gift card of $50. Ok so you gave me tax back.
Next visit was scheduled in May 2020 for alterations. Covid happen, appointment canceled. Was rescheduled to June 6. I called a few days prior to confirm my appointment. Due to pass experience there was no reminders. The receptionist had no appointment listed for me when I had the appointment in my email. They expected me to change my work schedule - which I already had to - to accommodate them. I demanded them to figure it out. Arrived for my alterations with Jo. I felt rushed obviously because she didn't realize that I had an appointment. I expressed the length of my dress was uneven. Her assistant was alerted by Jo, she responds "hold on - she's complaining about the dress". I told her it is not complaining if I'm telling you how I want my dress altered. Spent $400 on alterations. I come back today for my follow up. The sleeves sewed on were close to my choke line when I specifically said the lining of the strap. I even had a photo of it with Jo in the photo with the sleeves propped on accordingly. Now why would Jo sew the sleeves as she wishes where ever she proposed they were addressed when I have a photo indicating otherwise. So I sat there waiting for them to fix it. While another appointment arrive. I'm sitting outside. Frustrated waiting. Manager Melissa was making her circles. Asked me if I needed help. I expressed to her I have no clue what's going on. She checks up on the status. Concerned of what may be going on. I've already expressed my disappointment to Stephanie. What are you going to do? Nothing. Reprimand the employees? Whoopie. My god I really hate this place...like legit, everytime I have gone, I am filled with rage. The only reason I bumped my 1 star to a 2 star rating is because my bridesmaid had a decent experience....but here's the main reasons for my frustration.

First of all their customer service is the worst! Most of their employees are either clueless/aloof or shady! The times that I have gone, they have have confused my appointments, left me to try on dresses by myself without any assistance, and have only steered me towards the most expensive dresses despite my constant vocalization and expression of what I am looking for and my price range. They also have even given me dresses to try on that have other people's hair and make up on it? I'm not a particularly high maintenanced person, but even that grossed me out. I also noticed a few of their employees do not measure you correctly. I had one employee constantly bringing me HUGE bridal gowns, and the second i asked for a smaller size, they fit perfectly. It just feels like they are legitimately only out to make a buck and to rope you into using their tailoring service as well. As a soon to be bride, and as a store catering to bridal events, your establishment should be working hard to please, cater to, and listen to your customers! Wedding dress shopping is difficult enough as it is without adding on poor customer service.

I dont know if all David's bridals operate this way or if this particular location is just severely lacking....either way, if you are looking for wedding dress and you're on a budget, stay away from here!!!</text>

I usually don't review, but after seeing so many negative reviews and having such a great experience, I thought I would. I went in with my three bridesmaids on a very busy Saturday morning, and we had a wonderful time. We did have to wait a little bit for someone to take us back to our changing rooms, but it left us plenty of time to look for the dresses I had saved and browse through other ones. Miguel was super helpful and friendly. Even though he was helping a couple people (super busy Saturday), he still paid us plenty of attention and made sure to check up on us, as well as grab different sizes if we needed them. He started calling around to other stores to get the correct size/color shipped to this store. Also, my bridesmaids wanted me to put on the dress I had already chosen and bought, just for fun. <review>Ok...... well first off i want to say that everyone here at this location was nice, my complaint has nothing to do with me being treated rudely or in a unprofessional manner. But man these dresses end up costing you and arm and a leg. I just cannot believe that such a huge retailer does not have these dresses ready and in ones size.
In my case for example i went into this db location about 2 or more months before the wedding ( i was a bridesmaid) the girl that helped me that first day told me "i am only going to show you dresses that will be ready in your size by the event date"!  I tried on maybe 3 dresses found one i liked and it fit PERFECT, all it would need is the hemming at the bottom of the dress. When i went to go pay i noticed she was ordering a size up, i questioned why she was ordering a bigger size if the one i tried on was perfect.  Her response  was " the sample dresses are stretched out from people trying them on, they stretch out 3 sizes too big" so apparently that is the norm, but i told her that i didnt want to spend alot in alterations, i would rather she order the size i tried on. We went back a forth a bit she seemed to be getting annoyed at me for questioning her.... she was never rude but you can tell i was stepping on her toes. She told me she had 11 years experience and that this was the right thing to do. So i caved and let her order the bigger size. So at that time i paid $130 for the dress and another $30 for the hem, because if you buy it when you first purchase the dress it is half off , if i wanted it later it would be $60, i felt a little pressured to buy it at that moment and couldn't think of someone else in that moment who could hem the dress for me so i got the hemming package.
A few days later i ended up going back because i wasnt comfortable with the size i ordered and spoke with the manager,  she had me try the dress on and agreed with me on the size, she said she would change the size but then came back to me and said that it was on backorder,  something the previous girl failed to mention and i call bs to that. So i was stuck with the original bigger size ordered.
A few weeks later my dress came in so i went to pick it up and try it on... and yes it was big. I asked to have someone come out from alterations and give me a quote as yo how much it would be to fix, she told me all i needed was the shoulder taken up $20, and the waist taken in $50 . I didnt think it was that bad and came in the following week for my alterations appointment.  They pinned everything that needed fixing and at the end i was with with a bill for $140 and they still needed to add tax which came out to $150 something!!!!!!! How in the hell am i gonna pay more in alterations then i did for the dress. I had no words!! And now i had to get it done there because i had already paied for then hem and i wouldnt get my dress until 2 days before the wedding if i wanted it sooner i would need to pay a rush order of $25. This dress cost me over $300!!!!!!! I am a mother of 3 kids $300 could have bought ALOT. In the end i tried to make a positive and thought if nothing else this dress should fit me perfectly!!!!
Again i was sadly mistaken...... i picked up my dress and tries it on and it felt loose around the right side under my arm i pointed it out and told them i didnt feel comfortable  and they reassured me that it was ok and i didnt want it tighter. I asked again if they were sure because according to them these dresses stretch out and i didnt want to worry the day of the wedding..........so guess what happened the day of the wedding it was loose it kept slipping down and you could see a good part or my corset underneath . I was panicking  and pissed. Another bridesmaid had to safety pin my dress to my corset to hold it in place. After spending $150 on alterations.  Terrible work,!!!! Not happy at all didnt feel comfortable all day!</review>< Pics>

My daughter and I went to David's bridal yesterday with her best friend and her family because they are both getting married.  I was looking forward to this adventure so much.  Unfortunately, I have never been so disappointed.  Instead of having us around a raised dais so we could see the brides, they put us in a hallway.  It went downhill from there. They assigned us a guy who really didn't listen to what my daughter wanted.  She told him she hated spaghetti straps and he brought several dresses with them.  He never asked anything About her.  He just started bringing dresses.  Unfortunately we didn't have a woman assistant to help us get my daughter dressed in the gowns so we had to help her.  There was no element of surprise.  The Salon/store was shabby, the chairs worn and uncomfortable and they never offered us a wAter or anything.  It is supposed to be a joyous time and it was more than a let down.  When my daughter told him she wanted a low back, he said there wasn't any in her price range which was $1000.  Her friends budget was $500 and he brought her one. All in all, a very disappointing day.  We won't be back.  Oh btw, my daughter got a text this am saying that you were sorry she missed her appointment!!!   REALLY!!!! <review>I have since gotten married in my wonderful dress, but below please share with me my fear and anxiety over trying to have my dress ready in time!!

I have had too many problems with all 4 of my visits to David's Bridal. I have had problems getting my dress. I STILL don't have it and probably won't until a couple of days before my wedding. The wrong size was ordered for me, and when it came, it was shoved into a little box in a plastic bag. It was wadded up. I took it in for alterations and that's when it was discovered that it was way too big. The size I originally tried on before purchase fit beautifully and more than one person said I would require minimal alterations. When I went for it, the alterations folks said it was going to be a lot of work and a lot of money to alter because it was so big. They ordered me a new one in the size I need. And WHY does it take 3 weeks to ship? Especially when it was a David's Bridal mistake? I now have the stress of wondering if my dress will be ready for my day! It's nerve-wracking. Additionally, my bridesmaids were not treated well at all when they went to get their dresses. I was with two of them for their purchase and it was like pulling teeth to get any help, any questions answered, etc. She would disappear and not return for a long time. Then at the desk nobody could find my name in the system. This also happed for my maid of honor at another location. They couldn't find my name. Even though I'd bought an $800 gown and 3 bridesmaids dresses, they can never find record of me. Or they did the once, then it was "gone" again the next time.
I have already told many family members, bridal party friends about how horrible the experience was. The very first time I went in, it was awesome. I had a great sales person. She informed me during the visit that I was her last bride on her last day of employment there. Too bad. She really DID make me feel special. The time I went and actually bought the dress, I was the girl's first bride ever. And she was nice. I don't blame her. The people that ordered the dress incorrectly and packaged it so poorly are to blame. And now, on what is the last 20 days before my wedding, I am just hoping that I get to wear the dress that I fell in love with and spent so much money on.
I will not recommend this to anyone because it's just too eratic. Too unpredictable what kind of service one can get and if they can actually come out with the dress of their dreams in a timely manner and the bridesmaids should have been treated like more than second-class citizens.</review>< user>
